Police in Mt Fletcher have appealed to the public to assist with information that can lead them to the parents/mother of a 4-month-old baby girl, who was found at Mt Fletcher Taxi Rank on the 19th of May 2017. According to police, the baby girl was found at about 19:00 by a passer-by. "The baby girl was found without any identification or clinic-card that could help to identify the child," police said. "She was given the name, BONOLO MAY by the Mt Fletcher Hospital. "The child has been under hospital care since she was found." Anyone who has information about the whereabouts of her parents/mother should contact Detective Sergeant Qotywa at Mt Fletcher SAPS on 039 257 0 242/020 or 078 121 8735 or Crime Stop 0860010111.